WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:10.000
সাইট খুঁজে না পেলে ব্রাউজারে লিখুন:
-=[ MyFlixBD.com ]=-

00:13.400 --> 00:16.400
[Bagai] This is
a very serious charge against you, sir.

00:16.480 --> 00:19.320
Criminal intimidation, no less.

00:19.400 --> 00:20.840
Do you understand?

00:20.920 --> 00:23.680
According to this,
you made threats against the complainant.

00:23.760 --> 00:25.760
Sir, that's completely false.

00:26.800 --> 00:29.120
How could I ever threaten anyone?

00:29.200 --> 00:30.200
Correct.

00:30.280 --> 00:33.480
[defendant] I'd gone to ask him
to return my own money.

00:33.560 --> 00:36.960
Just because I used a few bad words,
he filed a case against me.

00:37.040 --> 00:38.080
[Bagai] A few bad words?

00:38.680 --> 00:40.040
Listen to me, my friend.

00:40.120 --> 00:42.040
You may have a sweet little voice,

00:42.120 --> 00:46.280
but those were some salty, bad words
you used on him, and they weren't a few.

00:47.640 --> 00:50.400
Bail will be difficult. Very difficult.

00:50.480 --> 00:53.240
But the previous lawyer said I was sure
to get bail.

00:53.320 --> 00:55.920
- The case is a done deal.
- Hey, genius,

00:56.000 --> 00:58.480
a case is never considered a done deal…

00:58.560 --> 01:00.640
until the judge says so.

01:00.720 --> 01:03.640
In the temple of the court,
the judge is God.

01:03.720 --> 01:07.240
And your case is
with Principal District Judge Tyagi.

01:07.320 --> 01:08.800
He's just been made judge.

01:10.040 --> 01:11.880
He won't let you off so easily.

01:13.080 --> 01:16.880
Sir, do something
and get me out on bail, please.

01:16.960 --> 01:20.520
You have no idea what I suffer in jail
because of my high-pitched voice.

01:20.600 --> 01:22.000
You can ask him.

01:22.960 --> 01:23.960
Yeah, he's right.

01:26.360 --> 01:27.920
It'll be 25,000.

01:28.000 --> 01:29.520
25,000?

01:30.880 --> 01:32.440
- Your Honour, first day.
- Yes.

01:32.520 --> 01:33.960
- Excited?
- Yes.

01:34.040 --> 01:35.640
Your Honour, this way.

01:36.360 --> 01:37.360
Why this way?

01:37.440 --> 01:38.880
Judges always enter from here.

01:39.400 --> 01:41.240
Topo, this is my first day.

01:41.840 --> 01:43.280
I won't just enter.

01:43.800 --> 01:45.920
I'm going to make a dramatic entrance.

01:50.120 --> 01:51.400
Hey, the judge is here.

01:51.480 --> 01:53.640
- Good morning, Your Honour.
- Sir, good morning.

01:54.720 --> 01:55.920
[employee] Good morning, sir.

02:11.520 --> 02:13.360
[employee 2] Hey, did you see that?
The judge just smiled.

02:13.440 --> 02:14.840
[employee 3] And that too at a lawyer.

02:14.920 --> 02:17.000
[employee 4] Looks like Bagai's bail
is a done deal.

02:20.560 --> 02:21.960
- [Maya] Good morning.
- Good morning.

02:29.520 --> 02:31.680
- Sit down please.
- Yes, sir.

02:31.760 --> 02:32.920
- [Topo] Your Honour.
- Yes?

02:33.000 --> 02:34.880
Why did you smile at that lawyer outside?

02:35.600 --> 02:36.640
[Tyagi] Huh?

02:38.480 --> 02:39.480
Huh?

02:42.440 --> 02:43.560
Smile?

02:58.600 --> 03:00.600
[air pump blowing]

03:04.520 --> 03:07.920
Mintu, sir, at least have a look. I stayed
up all night blowing balloons for you.

03:12.080 --> 03:13.640
[cries]

03:13.720 --> 03:15.240
Happy birthday, Mintu.

03:15.320 --> 03:18.720
Unbelievable! Birthday wishes and no gift?
Go sit outside in the foyer.

03:18.800 --> 03:20.800
Shambhu, only the ones
with the gifts will stay.

03:20.880 --> 03:23.040
Okay? These flowers are fake.
They won't do.

03:23.120 --> 03:25.360
I have sent an RS to everyone.
Don't forget to VP.

03:25.440 --> 03:27.160
Our Bar President will cut
his cake this evening.

03:27.240 --> 03:28.280
Acting Bar President.

03:28.360 --> 03:30.760
[colleague 1] We came to have cake
and he kicked us out.

03:30.840 --> 03:33.480
- [colleague 2] He always does…
- [Sujata] No sarcasm? No cutting comeback?

03:33.560 --> 03:35.280
Mintu's become mature.

03:36.200 --> 03:37.880
He is missing Visheshwar.

03:38.480 --> 03:39.840
Not at all, Mr Munshi.

03:40.560 --> 03:42.160
What does Tyagi mean to me?

03:42.240 --> 03:44.080
[chuckles] I mean,
he's a big-shot judge now.

03:44.680 --> 03:48.080
Why should he remember the birthday
of a small-time lawyer like me?

03:48.760 --> 03:51.200
So, Mintu, what kind of cake
would you like me to order?

03:51.840 --> 03:53.680
There will be no cake-cutting, Sujata.

03:53.760 --> 03:55.600
Tyagi gets me a cake every year.

03:55.680 --> 03:57.480
If he doesn't this time,
then I won't have one.

03:58.280 --> 03:59.640
He doesn't understand.

03:59.720 --> 04:02.320
Visheshwar is a judge now.
He can't meet him.

04:03.600 --> 04:05.600
[phone buzzing]

04:08.080 --> 04:09.080
Yeah, Vishwas?

04:09.160 --> 04:10.680
[Vishwas] Sujata,
something's happened to Law.

04:10.760 --> 04:12.520
- What happened to Law?
- [bell rings]

04:12.600 --> 04:18.480
[Law] What I'm about to tell you is
something that happens to a lot of men.

04:19.320 --> 04:20.400
Promise me…

04:22.080 --> 04:24.720
- you won't laugh at me.
- [Vishwas] No, bro, we won't laugh.

04:24.800 --> 04:27.920
- Don't worry, Law. This is a safe space.
- [Daleel] Mmm.

04:28.880 --> 04:32.280
This morning, when I…

04:33.160 --> 04:36.760
was going up in the lift
with some bread and eggs, I met…

04:38.160 --> 04:39.400
Mrs Sharma there.

04:39.480 --> 04:40.880
Mrs Sharma?

04:40.960 --> 04:42.680
- My landlord.
- Landlady.

04:42.760 --> 04:44.440
She is no lady, Ani.

04:45.400 --> 04:48.200
What she did to me in the lift, no…

04:48.280 --> 04:50.080
No lady would ever do that.

04:50.160 --> 04:52.240
- [Vishwas] Hmm?
- [Law] She actually…

04:53.440 --> 04:54.480
spanked me.

04:54.560 --> 04:55.840
- [grunts]
- [gasps]

04:56.920 --> 04:59.920
- [Vishwas] Fuck.
- What the hell do you mean by "spank"?

05:00.000 --> 05:02.560
Daleel, "spank" means to, uh…

05:04.120 --> 05:05.200
pat someone.

05:06.200 --> 05:09.000
So, now this prude doesn't like
being patted on the back?

05:09.600 --> 05:11.800
Actually, it was lower than the back.

05:11.880 --> 05:13.320
- On the waist?
- [clicks tongue]

05:13.400 --> 05:17.520
- Lower than that.
- Oh, I see, I see! [chuckles]

05:18.440 --> 05:19.520
[Sujata] Come on, Law.

05:19.600 --> 05:21.080
Who does that nowadays?

05:21.160 --> 05:23.120
- It must have been a mistake.
- [Vishwas] Just ask me.

05:23.200 --> 05:25.160
- I'm always getting spanked in the metro.
- [Daleel] Mm-hmm.

05:25.240 --> 05:26.480
The old guys spank the hardest.

05:26.560 --> 05:29.160
If her hand had touched me by mistake,
she would have moved it away, right?

05:29.240 --> 05:30.320
She didn't?

05:30.400 --> 05:32.280
- Hers was stuck to my butt.
- [gasps]

05:32.360 --> 05:34.320
Right up to the eighth floor.

05:34.960 --> 05:37.240
And you know what?
She didn't raise my rent this year.

05:37.320 --> 05:38.640
She reduced it.

05:39.200 --> 05:41.040
But that wasn't a discount.

05:42.800 --> 05:43.880
It was a payment.

05:43.960 --> 05:47.800
You fool. If you're getting paid for it,
then what the hell is your problem?

05:47.880 --> 05:50.120
Daleel, why are you being so insensitive?

05:50.640 --> 05:52.360
Law needs our help.

05:52.440 --> 05:54.480
- He's been harassed, okay?
- [Daleel] Mm-hmm.

05:54.560 --> 05:57.240
Her-ass I've heard of.
Who's ever heard of his-ass?

05:57.320 --> 05:58.840
She… She means something else.

05:58.920 --> 06:01.440
- [Law] I knew no one would believe me.
- What does she mean?

06:01.960 --> 06:04.880
It's like those harassment victims
in the movies. Just like that!

06:04.960 --> 06:08.160
Those are movie stars.
Why would anyone harass you?

06:08.240 --> 06:10.640
- Law isn't even your real name.
- [Daleel] Mm-hmm.

06:10.720 --> 06:12.600
- Even stars don't use their real names.
- [Daleel] He's right.

06:12.680 --> 06:14.360
Yeah, I'm forgetting who,
but there's lots of them.

06:14.440 --> 06:15.840
- Like that guy--
- Guys, please.

06:16.800 --> 06:17.840
Focus.

06:17.920 --> 06:19.640
[cries]

06:19.720 --> 06:20.920
Law, I believe you.

06:22.120 --> 06:25.600
And I'll make sure that you
and men like you feel safe in our society.

06:25.680 --> 06:26.680
You have full right.

06:27.880 --> 06:31.160
So, this happened to you
in your building elevator?

06:32.840 --> 06:34.720
Any CCTV cameras?

06:36.320 --> 06:38.440
- For sure.
- [colleague] Now, you tell me.

06:38.520 --> 06:41.000
What kind of smile did Bagai receive?

06:41.560 --> 06:45.640
A very personal one.
And Judge Tyagi nodded his head.

06:45.720 --> 06:48.120
Now, when a smile was so personal,

06:48.200 --> 06:50.480
then the judgement will
also be in his favour, right?

06:50.560 --> 06:52.240
[Bagai] Don't talk nonsense, my friend.

06:52.320 --> 06:55.360
Uh, Tyagi sir's
a very impartial judge, okay?

06:55.440 --> 06:58.720
And I won't hear
a single bad thing said against my friend.

06:58.800 --> 07:01.320
Bagai, sir, I was wrong.

07:01.400 --> 07:03.360
Twenty-five thousand is too little.

07:03.440 --> 07:04.560
I'll pay you 30.

07:06.560 --> 07:08.440
Out of all the cases on my plate,

07:08.520 --> 07:12.960
it is only in Bagai's case
that bail appears to be clearly justified.

07:13.680 --> 07:16.040
All the evidence is
in favour of his client.

07:16.120 --> 07:19.840
So, now can you please tell me, why should
I keep him in jail for a whole month?

07:19.920 --> 07:23.680
Well, someone has to pay
the price for that smile you gave, sir.

07:23.760 --> 07:27.120
- Otherwise, you will appear biased.
- Which I'm certainly not.

07:27.200 --> 07:31.480
None of us are, for that matter,
and neither should we appear so.

07:32.240 --> 07:36.520
What do you think? That I enjoy walking
around in court with a resting bitch face?

07:36.600 --> 07:37.880
[colleagues chuckle]

07:37.960 --> 07:39.880
It's a strategy, my friend.

07:40.440 --> 07:43.920
So the lawyers I meet
dare not smile at me.

07:44.000 --> 07:45.080
[colleagues chuckle]

07:45.160 --> 07:46.880
At least you've
just been accused of smiling.

07:46.960 --> 07:49.440
On my birthday,
my wife gifted me this fancy watch.

07:49.520 --> 07:52.960
I only glanced at it a couple of times
and someone complained

07:53.040 --> 07:55.160
that the judge is in a hurry
to deliver his judgement.

07:55.240 --> 07:56.480
[Shubhkela chuckles] Very true.

07:56.560 --> 08:00.840
Actions, reactions…
A judge is judged on everything.

08:00.920 --> 08:04.000
- A judge is always on trial.
- [chuckles] Correct.

08:04.080 --> 08:07.080
- So do you expect me to be like Mona Lisa?
- [colleague chuckles]

08:07.160 --> 08:10.200
Yeah, where no one can tell
whether I'm smiling or I'm not smiling?

08:10.280 --> 08:14.320
Bureaucrats and politicians are
never questioned when they are smiling.

08:14.400 --> 08:17.920
Why are all these dos
and don'ts reserved only for judges?

08:18.000 --> 08:22.480
Because, at the end of it all,
the public comes to us.

08:22.560 --> 08:23.840
Looking for justice.

08:25.560 --> 08:30.520
That's why the PDJ of the court cannot
appear biased at any time.

08:31.320 --> 08:33.400
Just deny bail.

08:33.480 --> 08:35.200
[Tyagi] Look,
I don't want to appear biased.

08:35.800 --> 08:40.520
But I'm certainly not willing
to send an innocent to jail either.

08:40.600 --> 08:41.600
That's for sure.

08:44.520 --> 08:45.600
[Shubhkela] Now, Mr Tyagi,

08:47.200 --> 08:51.560
what if Bagai withdraws this case himself?

08:52.360 --> 08:55.400
- Meaning what?
- Meaning, what if…

08:55.920 --> 08:58.480
Bagai himself withdraws this case.
What then?

09:10.800 --> 09:12.200
- Eight…
- [elevator dings]

09:13.320 --> 09:14.840
Right up to the eighth floor.

09:14.920 --> 09:19.320
[chuckles] It's not just America
that's naughty. India's naughty too!

09:19.400 --> 09:21.640
Put it on the Internet. It'll go viral.

09:21.720 --> 09:24.200
What should go viral
is your response to this.

09:24.280 --> 09:27.080
Is this any way for the police
to deal with a crime?

09:27.160 --> 09:29.400
Huh, crime? What crime?

09:29.480 --> 09:32.320
You're a lawyer, right?
Tell me which law does this come under.

09:32.400 --> 09:35.880
Ah, ah, sir. She's from Harvard, sir.
She'll tell you. Go on, tell him.

09:35.960 --> 09:38.920
What can she tell me?
Even the Chief Justice doesn't know.

09:39.000 --> 09:40.760
Because no law has been broken.

09:41.360 --> 09:43.880
Madam, there's a law only for eve-teasing.

09:43.960 --> 09:46.120
Because "Adam" teases Eve.

09:46.200 --> 09:48.000
There's no such thing as Adam-teasing.

09:48.080 --> 09:51.000
By law, only women are harassment victims.

09:51.080 --> 09:52.960
Sir, a victim is a victim.

09:53.040 --> 09:55.480
I don't believe I'm going
to say this, but…

09:55.560 --> 09:57.600
- What about men's rights?
- [Pepsu] Huh?

09:57.680 --> 09:58.880
Don't they have enough already?

09:59.480 --> 10:00.800
What about our rights?

10:00.880 --> 10:02.720
Ma'am, it's not a competition.

10:02.800 --> 10:07.280
How true. We register
36 offences against women daily.

10:07.360 --> 10:09.880
And men? Once in 36 months.

10:09.960 --> 10:11.320
Of course there's no competition.

10:11.920 --> 10:15.200
Ma'am, I fully concur
with your outrage. I really do.

10:15.920 --> 10:18.080
But what happened
with Law was wrong too, right?

10:18.160 --> 10:20.320
Yes, but how do we know
this complaint isn't fake?

10:20.400 --> 10:22.360
- But the video's right in front of you.
- Yes, sir.

10:22.440 --> 10:24.600
And where does the video show
that she didn't have his consent?

10:24.680 --> 10:26.960
But I'm telling you
I didn't consent to that, sir.

10:27.040 --> 10:29.440
- [Vishwas] Mm-hmm.
- Sir, Law's modesty has been outraged.

10:29.520 --> 10:32.640
Madam, the law assumes
that men simply don't have modesty.

10:32.720 --> 10:34.320
So, how can this Law have any?

10:34.400 --> 10:36.600
You tell me. Do we men have any modesty?

10:36.680 --> 10:39.560
Men don't have modesty, only mortality.

10:39.640 --> 10:41.600
- [Pepsu] Of course.
- [gasps] What are you saying?

10:41.680 --> 10:45.000
Officer, okay,
so we don't have a law for this.

10:45.080 --> 10:48.400
What about intimidation,
assault, pickpocketing…

10:48.480 --> 10:50.200
We could at least file charges
under one of these.

10:50.280 --> 10:52.080
- What do you mean?
- One second.

10:52.720 --> 10:54.720
You want the police
to bring false charges against her?

10:54.800 --> 10:56.560
- Yes, of course. No.
- No, no, not at all.

10:56.640 --> 10:59.200
- How could I do that?
- Ma'am, there's no such clause, right?

10:59.720 --> 11:01.240
Then tell me.
What is poor Law going to do?

11:01.320 --> 11:03.160
He'll learn to put up with it.

11:03.240 --> 11:06.960
Women are always posting about being
groped on social media and moving on.

11:07.040 --> 11:08.560
You can also make a few posts.

11:09.160 --> 11:10.960
- Dude, wanna do that?
- Okay. Look, guys.

11:11.040 --> 11:12.360
We never discriminate.

11:13.240 --> 11:17.280
In cases like this, the advice we give
to women, I'll give the same to you.

11:19.360 --> 11:20.360
Find a new place.

11:20.960 --> 11:22.440
- Oh!
- That's it.

11:23.040 --> 11:27.520
- So, this is your advice to women?
- What's wrong with that?

11:27.600 --> 11:29.600
- I mean, how can you ask a victim--
- Okay.

11:31.280 --> 11:34.280
There's no solution, right?
Then I'll find a new place.

11:34.360 --> 11:37.000
- [Vishwas] Be a man, dude.
- [Pepsu] Wonderful.

11:37.080 --> 11:38.680
\- [knocks on door]
- [Bagai] Good afternoon, Your Honour.

11:38.760 --> 11:39.760
\PREMCHAND
GABAN

11:39.840 --> 11:41.280
You asked for me?

11:41.960 --> 11:44.520
No, I didn't, Mr Bagai. He did, Mr Tyagi.

11:45.560 --> 11:47.680
[Bagai] Oh, Tyagi, sir.

11:47.760 --> 11:49.960
You could have called me
to your chamber, Your Honour.

11:52.120 --> 11:55.400
That is one mistake
I will never make, Mr Bagai.

11:55.480 --> 11:57.720
But I have a favour to ask of you.

11:57.800 --> 11:59.680
Your wish is my command.

11:59.760 --> 12:02.120
Please apply for an exception in my court.

12:02.920 --> 12:06.800
After that, we can happily continue
to exchange smile for smile.

12:06.880 --> 12:08.480
Exception, Tyagi, sir?

12:09.200 --> 12:12.520
You mean, none of my cases will come
before you in court?

12:12.600 --> 12:13.640
But why?

12:13.720 --> 12:15.120
"Why?"

12:15.720 --> 12:18.320
Do you know what people are
saying about us on campus?

12:19.000 --> 12:20.640
That I, uh…

12:20.720 --> 12:21.800
[chuckles]

12:25.000 --> 12:26.120
That I, uh…

12:26.840 --> 12:28.000
I like you.

12:28.080 --> 12:30.640
So? You don't like me, Tyagi, sir?

12:30.720 --> 12:34.840
Of course I do like you,
but not… not in that way.

12:34.920 --> 12:36.960
Then in what way exactly do you like me?

12:37.040 --> 12:38.240
What are you being so coy?

12:38.320 --> 12:40.240
- You know exactly in what way.
- [chuckles]

12:40.320 --> 12:42.560
[chuckling] No, I don't.
Why don't you explain it to me?

12:42.640 --> 12:44.880
[Shubhkela chuckling]

12:44.960 --> 12:47.200
You both are talking
about exceptions, right?

12:47.280 --> 12:50.360
- Uh, of course, uh, Mr Shubhkela.
- [Shubhkela chuckling] Keep going.

12:50.440 --> 12:53.640
- Keep going.
- Look, Bagai, don't beat around the bush.

12:54.160 --> 12:56.960
Are you willing
to do me this favour or not?

12:57.040 --> 13:00.560
Of course, Your Honour.
I will take an exception.

13:01.200 --> 13:03.800
But, uh, you'll be setting
the wrong precedent.

13:04.400 --> 13:08.720
Look, just like me, there are many other
lawyers you like very much, isn't it?

13:09.480 --> 13:12.200
After all, you were our president, right?

13:12.280 --> 13:15.240
Will you ask all of them
to take an exception?

13:16.000 --> 13:19.880
At this rate, you will not have
any cases in your court, Your Honour.

13:20.760 --> 13:23.400
That's, um, very true, Mr Tyagi.

13:26.640 --> 13:29.760
So you're looking out for me.
Thank you, Mr Bagai.

13:29.840 --> 13:34.000
In friendship,
there's no "sorry" and no "thank you".

13:34.080 --> 13:35.080
I'll take your leave.

13:39.920 --> 13:41.160
What's with this guy?

13:41.240 --> 13:43.480
[chuckling] Never mind that.

13:44.120 --> 13:45.520
What will you do now?

13:46.120 --> 13:48.000
Will you grant bail or not?

13:50.200 --> 13:52.000
Mintu, sir!

13:53.320 --> 13:54.920
Happy birthday!

13:55.000 --> 13:56.760
It's not my birthday!

13:56.840 --> 13:58.880
- It is, it is. It is his birthday.
- What a weirdo.

13:58.960 --> 14:00.240
[muttering] Happy Birthday…

14:00.320 --> 14:03.520
You know, I think you are judging
Tyagi sir too harshly.

14:04.120 --> 14:05.440
It's only his first day as a judge.

14:05.520 --> 14:07.360
He must have forgotten
with all the new work pressure.

14:08.240 --> 14:09.240
Just wait,

14:09.320 --> 14:11.440
- as soon as he sees you, he'll--
- [vehicle horn beeping]

14:12.480 --> 14:13.600
JALJEERA
LEMON JUICE

14:13.680 --> 14:14.880
Mintu, sir.

14:14.960 --> 14:16.200
[horn honks]

14:47.800 --> 14:50.080
[Law] I have sent the eviction notice
an hour ago.

14:50.680 --> 14:53.160
Mrs Sharma has seen it
but hasn't responded.

14:53.240 --> 14:54.640
[Sujata] Next time, pay the full rent.

14:54.720 --> 14:57.720
Cheap homes only exist
in horror films or porn films.

14:59.560 --> 15:02.040
Can you guys help me move out of my flat?

15:05.800 --> 15:06.800
I'll accompany you.

15:08.000 --> 15:18.000
Downloaded from -=[ MyFlixBD.com ]=-

15:11.640 --> 15:13.000
It's the least that I can do.

15:13.080 --> 15:15.440
Because, by virtue of being a woman,

15:16.400 --> 15:18.640
I can understand
what you're going through.

15:18.720 --> 15:19.920
- I really can.
- [Shambhu] Madam!

15:20.800 --> 15:22.040
Anyone here named Nikunj?

15:22.120 --> 15:23.280
- [Vishwas] Huh?
- Why?

15:23.360 --> 15:26.160
- [Shambhu] They're looking for him.
- He has been charged under section 354.

15:27.400 --> 15:29.440
[siren wails]

15:29.520 --> 15:30.520
[Vishwas] Here's my ID.

15:30.600 --> 15:33.040
- Outraging a woman's modesty?
- I'll show you my driving licence also.

15:33.120 --> 15:35.360
- Woman's modesty? Tell me, Daleel.
- Look, here it is.

15:35.440 --> 15:37.560
Does your identity card have
the name Nikunj on it?

15:37.640 --> 15:39.600
Why would my name be Nikunj?
What's wrong with you?

15:39.680 --> 15:42.520
- I told you, there's no Nikunj here.
- No, no, there is someone.

15:42.600 --> 15:44.160
- [Sujata] Really?
- Yeah, I made his court ID.

15:44.240 --> 15:47.080
Arrest that horrible pervert!
That is Nikunj.

15:48.480 --> 15:50.800
- Oh, he is Nikunj.
- Your name's Nikunj?

15:50.880 --> 15:53.920
- [officer] Hey, you harass women?
- No, no… No, I didn't do anything, sir!

15:54.000 --> 15:56.000
Sir, I didn't do anything. I swear. Ma'am!

15:56.080 --> 15:58.520
- Sir, one second.
- Ma'am… Ma'am, I didn't do anything.

15:58.600 --> 16:00.040
I didn't do anything, ma'am.

16:00.120 --> 16:01.120
- Officer…
- [Law] Do something.

16:01.200 --> 16:02.640
Tell me.

16:02.720 --> 16:03.920
[Mrs Sharma clears throat]

16:04.560 --> 16:05.840
I'm single.

16:06.480 --> 16:07.880
A divorcee.

16:08.960 --> 16:11.680
But… I'm a little friendly by nature.

16:12.600 --> 16:16.840
My daughter lives far away in Australia.
And Nikunj…

16:16.920 --> 16:19.080
- Sir, I swear I didn't do anything…
- Hey, you be quiet.

16:19.160 --> 16:20.600
Hold on. Hold on. Let her speak.

16:20.680 --> 16:24.280
Young man, after all, far away from home.

16:24.840 --> 16:27.760
And yes,
not a single girl has ever visited him.

16:27.840 --> 16:30.080
- What?
- Loser.

16:30.880 --> 16:32.360
- Not even one?
- It's possible

16:32.440 --> 16:34.680
all his pent-up feelings
are bubbling up inside.

16:34.760 --> 16:36.400
And maybe that's why he said,

16:38.120 --> 16:39.120
"Aunty…

16:39.920 --> 16:41.640
- could you please pat me?"
- Huh?

16:41.720 --> 16:44.920
- Uh, no…
- "A little lower than my back."

16:45.600 --> 16:48.560
I'm single, a divorcee,

16:48.640 --> 16:50.440
- a little--
- A little friendly by nature.

16:50.520 --> 16:52.320
- Sir, she's playing Uno Reverse.
- What reverse?

16:52.400 --> 16:54.280
Mrs Sharma, how shameless are you?

16:54.360 --> 16:57.480
It's because of women like her,
that people don't believe the victim, sir.

16:57.560 --> 16:59.160
Sir, you know very well that she is lying.

16:59.240 --> 17:00.400
- Exactly.
- She has no proof at all.

17:00.480 --> 17:01.760
[Pepsu] Yes, yes, I know that.

17:01.840 --> 17:04.320
- Yes, ma'am.
- Madam, it's a woman's complaint.

17:04.400 --> 17:05.400
A woman!

17:05.480 --> 17:08.880
Never mind him. Even if a women complains
against a parrot, we take action.

17:08.960 --> 17:12.200
- Yeah, he's right about that.
- Police report first, proof later.

17:12.280 --> 17:13.360
[all] Hmm.

17:13.440 --> 17:15.400
Being a woman has advantages these days.

17:15.480 --> 17:17.480
[chuckling] Yeah, ma'am,
you're right about that.

17:17.560 --> 17:18.680
Excuse me.

17:18.760 --> 17:21.040
This is not feminism.

17:21.120 --> 17:22.640
- Yeah.
- Sir, Inspector Pepsu,

17:22.720 --> 17:23.880
please don't file a report.

17:23.960 --> 17:26.400
If he ever goes in for an arranged
marriage, it will get in the way.

17:26.480 --> 17:29.520
And if he does get married,
he won't even cross the border.

17:30.200 --> 17:31.960
- He'll never get a visa.
- Exactly.

17:32.040 --> 17:34.000
- Sir, I'd like to go--
- [Pepsu] So, this is my advice to you.

17:34.080 --> 17:36.480
Apologise to her and settle the matter.

17:36.560 --> 17:38.080
- What kind of advice is--
- Absolutely not.

17:38.160 --> 17:39.600
You file your report.

17:39.680 --> 17:41.400
- Nikunj, we're going to see them in court.
- Yeah.

17:41.480 --> 17:42.480
Yeah, not going to apologise.

17:42.560 --> 17:45.320
- Go ahead. File the report. Do it.
- He's a gone case. Take him away.

17:45.400 --> 17:47.960
- There's no way he's going to apologise--
- Sorry… Sorry, ma'am.

17:48.040 --> 17:51.120
It was my fault, Mrs Sharma.
I'll never do it again. Please. Please.

17:51.200 --> 17:53.560
- Don't do that--
- Hey! What are you doing?

17:53.640 --> 17:54.800
Okay, I won't file a report.

17:54.880 --> 17:56.760
Oh, ow. My back!

17:56.840 --> 17:58.560
Okay, let her go. She won't do it.

17:58.640 --> 18:01.640
- Listen, son, I won't file a report.
- [Pepsu] She won't do it.

18:01.720 --> 18:03.800
- Promise?
- Yes, yes, I promise.

18:05.640 --> 18:07.440
- But on one condition.
- [Law] Yes.

18:10.240 --> 18:12.160
- You won't move out.
- Yeah.

18:17.240 --> 18:21.360
Uh, it was really hard finding,
uh, a tenant. Uh…

18:21.440 --> 18:24.520
As you know by now, I am single,

18:24.600 --> 18:28.720
a divorcee, a little friendly by nature.

18:28.800 --> 18:30.000
[Vishwas] Oh, my God.

18:31.640 --> 18:32.840
DISTRICT COURT, PATPARGANJ

18:32.920 --> 18:34.960
- What time does he leave?
- There's no fixed time, sir.

18:35.040 --> 18:37.720
Sir! Tyagi, sir!
I know you saw me standing here.

18:38.960 --> 18:40.280
Let him in.

18:41.960 --> 18:44.040
Sir, you've forgotten
what day it is today.

18:44.120 --> 18:45.120
[Tyagi shushes]

18:45.640 --> 18:47.320
These are the judges' chambers.

18:48.880 --> 18:50.400
- Sorry, sir.
- [Tyagi] Tell me.

18:51.280 --> 18:52.840
Sir, it's Mintu's birthday today.

18:52.920 --> 18:54.320
Yes, I know that.

18:55.240 --> 18:57.720
But, sir, he's… he's very upset actually.

18:57.800 --> 18:59.760
He refuses to even cut a free cake.

18:59.840 --> 19:02.840
He says "My friends cut me off,
so why should I cut a cake?"

19:04.760 --> 19:05.800
Sorry, sir.

19:05.880 --> 19:06.880
Order, not now.

19:06.960 --> 19:10.640
It's my first day as a judge, and word has
already spread that I am biased.

19:10.720 --> 19:13.320
And you want me to meet Mintu
and sing happy birthday to him?

19:13.400 --> 19:16.360
No, sir, no need to sing.
Just say it normally. That'll be enough.

19:19.240 --> 19:21.520
But, sir, he has a right
to be upset, doesn't he?

19:21.600 --> 19:23.320
On the one hand, you're ignoring him.

19:23.400 --> 19:26.720
On the other, you're flashing
smiles at that wonky-toothed Bagai.

19:26.800 --> 19:29.360
I didn't do it on purpose, man.
I saw him and I just smiled.

19:29.440 --> 19:31.000
Now what do I do? I made a mistake.

19:31.920 --> 19:35.040
Since you've already made one mistake,
why don't you make one more?

19:35.120 --> 19:36.680
Do it for Mintu's sake.

19:41.880 --> 19:43.320
Make one more mistake?

19:45.920 --> 19:47.880
- Your Honour, the list is ready.
- [Tyagi] Mmm.

19:47.960 --> 19:51.480
The advocates today are,
Mr Advait Khurana, Parul Gulati,

19:51.560 --> 19:53.320
and, uh, B.K. Zaveri…

19:53.880 --> 19:55.360
Mr Zaveri.

19:57.000 --> 19:58.240
Mr Zaveri!

19:59.080 --> 20:01.720
Oh, wow! You're looking slim and trim!

20:01.800 --> 20:03.360
[chuckling] Are you on a diet?

20:05.000 --> 20:07.040
He's a lean and clean lawyer.

20:13.680 --> 20:16.560
History of criminal behaviour.
Bail denied.

20:30.080 --> 20:33.080
Application unmaintainable. Bail denied.

20:43.360 --> 20:45.280
Chance of absconding. Bail denied.

20:46.880 --> 20:50.520
The ones he smiled at,
only receive a smile, no bail.

20:55.960 --> 20:57.920
What's the matter, Mr Bagai?

20:59.440 --> 21:00.920
Why do you look so scared?

21:02.040 --> 21:03.440
I don't see your smile today.

21:03.520 --> 21:05.440
[chuckles] Nothing's the matter,
Your Honour.

21:05.520 --> 21:08.000
What do you think? Should he get bail?

21:08.080 --> 21:10.080
Now that,
only you can decide, Your Honour.

21:10.160 --> 21:12.880
But you're a lawyer too. You tell me.

21:13.480 --> 21:17.280
If he deserves bail, then tell me why.

21:18.480 --> 21:21.880
It's his very first offence, sir.
Uh, it won't happen again.

21:30.520 --> 21:31.520
Bail granted.

21:38.440 --> 21:39.680
See, I told you.

21:40.200 --> 21:43.800
Judge Tyagi's smile and judgement
are both totally unbiased.

21:43.880 --> 21:46.000
Come on,
now give me back my money, hurry up.

21:48.840 --> 21:50.800
[Vishwas] This poor guy spent
five years studying.

21:51.600 --> 21:54.800
He then passed the Bar Council exam.
He became a lawyer.

21:55.640 --> 21:57.320
And still, he's so helpless.

21:58.120 --> 21:59.960
Imagine what the common man
would go through.

22:00.480 --> 22:03.080
- Just think about it.
- Excuse me, can I have another plate?

22:08.720 --> 22:12.200
I empathise with you, Law. I really do.

22:18.680 --> 22:19.920
Feels great.

22:21.000 --> 22:22.280
You were right, Sujata.

22:23.520 --> 22:25.760
Arguments are just not enough to win.

22:30.520 --> 22:32.680
I do have a strategy in mind.

22:34.800 --> 22:37.920
It's a little dodgy, but…

22:40.920 --> 22:43.400
What is it, Inspector?
Why have you called me here?

22:43.480 --> 22:44.680
- Over there.
- [Vishwas] She is here.

22:44.760 --> 22:46.400
- Ma'am, here, please come, sit here.
- Go on.

22:46.480 --> 22:48.360
- Ma'am, you write the report.
- [officer] Mmm.

22:48.920 --> 22:50.920
What happened?
Why have you called me? What have I done?

22:51.000 --> 22:52.080
She was eve-teasing me.

22:52.160 --> 22:53.720
- Eves.
- Eves-teasing.

22:53.800 --> 22:55.200
- [Ani] Plural.
- What?

22:55.280 --> 22:58.720
Mrs Sharma has outraged
the modesty of both of us, ma'am.

22:58.800 --> 23:01.520
- So, you harassed them?
- Look, this is such a blatant lie.

23:01.600 --> 23:06.480
Neither do I know these two women,
and nor are these men young.

23:07.080 --> 23:08.360
[Sujata] Mrs Sharma, that is such a lie.

23:08.440 --> 23:11.000
She passed by us in the market
and stroked us like this.

23:11.800 --> 23:13.640
And then you know what she did?

23:13.720 --> 23:14.720
She winked at us.

23:14.800 --> 23:15.840
[gasps]

23:15.920 --> 23:17.680
- So, you winked at them?
- [Mrs Sharma] No…

23:17.760 --> 23:20.240
- It's a woman's complaint, madam.
- Woman!

23:20.320 --> 23:23.600
Have you forgotten?
Police report first, proof later.

23:24.200 --> 23:27.120
Besides, we have this video of you.

23:28.120 --> 23:29.840
Maybe we can't file a case,

23:29.920 --> 23:32.240
but a character certificate should be
good enough.

23:32.320 --> 23:33.720
[colleagues, officer] Hmm.

23:33.800 --> 23:37.200
So here is my advice to you.
Settle this amongst yourselves.

23:37.840 --> 23:40.200
- Thrash it out.
- No, ma'am, go ahead with the report.

23:40.840 --> 23:42.160
- Let's proceed.
- No, no, look…

23:42.240 --> 23:43.400
It was one o'clock, and it--

23:43.480 --> 23:45.080
- Look, please listen.
- No, we don't want to.

23:45.160 --> 23:47.280
- Let them finish.
- [Ani] There were a lot of people.

23:47.360 --> 23:50.560
- And there was a woman--
- Okay. I admit it, it was my fault.

23:51.120 --> 23:52.520
- Yes!
- Bro.

23:52.600 --> 23:54.560
- I knew it. [mutters]
- It was my fault entirely.

23:55.400 --> 23:57.520
I want to go to Australia
to see my daughter.

23:58.120 --> 23:59.520
I won't get a visa.

24:00.680 --> 24:03.160
Please, don't file a report.

24:04.000 --> 24:05.000
[Law] Okay.

24:05.640 --> 24:07.000
We won't file a report.

24:07.520 --> 24:09.280
[sighs]

24:09.360 --> 24:11.960
- But on one condition.
- What?

24:12.040 --> 24:13.880
One year rent-free.

24:16.360 --> 24:18.240
- With free parking.
- [Vishwas] Mm-hmm.

24:18.320 --> 24:19.400
Nikunj?

24:20.760 --> 24:22.200
Well done, bro.

24:24.120 --> 24:27.040
[Shambhu] Come on, come on.
We are cutting Mintu's cake!

24:27.120 --> 24:29.000
[colleagues] One, two…

24:29.080 --> 24:30.920
Happy birthday! [cheering]

24:31.000 --> 24:32.360
IT'S MY BIRTHDAY

24:35.400 --> 24:36.400
Nice.

24:37.360 --> 24:40.640
- Uh, whose idea was it?
- His!

24:40.720 --> 24:42.560
[all chuckling]

24:42.640 --> 24:44.120
- Very nice.
- Thanks.

24:47.840 --> 24:49.280
- It's my birthday!
- Yeah.

24:49.360 --> 24:51.640
- It's my birthday, guys! It's my birthday.
- Yeah.

24:51.720 --> 24:52.760
Yeah? Yeah?

24:52.840 --> 24:54.360
It's my birthday! Stop it!

24:55.240 --> 24:57.360
I've already said
I don't want to celebrate.

24:57.440 --> 24:59.640
So, why the hell have you
all turned up here?

25:03.320 --> 25:05.280
[Tyagi] What are you
so upset about, Mintu?

25:19.480 --> 25:21.000
What the hell, bro?

25:21.080 --> 25:22.240
Why are you so late?

25:22.320 --> 25:24.920
Because I wanted
to get this for you. Topo?

25:27.080 --> 25:29.600
[Mintu sighs, chuckles] Oh, man!

25:30.560 --> 25:32.120
Kidney-bean flavour! [chuckles]

25:32.200 --> 25:34.720
My girlfriend made it for you.
Kidney-bean and rice cake.

25:34.800 --> 25:37.600
[Tyagi] And one more thing,
Mr Lakhmir Singh Balli.

25:38.680 --> 25:40.400
I have an exception to declare.

25:41.480 --> 25:45.640
You, and of course,
any case from your chamber

25:46.280 --> 25:49.920
will never be admitted in my courtroom.

25:54.480 --> 25:58.440
You are my friend.
There's no way I can judge you.

26:00.360 --> 26:03.000
You said it
so that's how it will be. [sighs]

26:03.080 --> 26:06.760
- [exclaims] Happy birthday, bro!
- [Mintu chuckling]

26:06.840 --> 26:08.840
I love you, bro. Love you!

26:09.760 --> 26:11.040
This Tyagi guy is amazing.

26:11.680 --> 26:13.720
Thank you, Vishwas!

26:14.520 --> 26:18.320
All these years, we've been afraid to
smile, and here he is hugging in public.

26:18.400 --> 26:20.480
[all cheering]

26:23.360 --> 26:24.920
Happy birthday!

26:25.000 --> 26:26.960
Happy birthday to me!

26:28.320 --> 26:29.320
[Law] Ani.

26:32.680 --> 26:35.840
Listen, uh,
after what you did for me today,

26:35.920 --> 26:39.480
the least I can do is get you some coffee.

26:40.560 --> 26:42.840
Really? You won't have it with me?

26:42.920 --> 26:47.360
No, no, no, I will. What I really meant
was you and I can have it…

26:48.320 --> 26:49.720
[stammers] …together.

26:49.800 --> 26:51.320
Aw, that's so sweet.

26:51.960 --> 26:53.160
So, it's a date then?

26:53.920 --> 26:55.240
Yeah. I guess.

26:55.320 --> 26:56.800
Perfect. See you.

26:56.880 --> 26:57.880
See you.

26:58.400 --> 26:59.800
- Bye.
- Bye.

27:03.520 --> 27:04.760
Yes. Yes!

27:05.960 --> 27:07.040
Hey, Vishwas.

27:07.600 --> 27:09.680
- All good?
- Hey, bro. Can you push?

27:09.760 --> 27:11.360
- [Law] Yeah, sure.
- It… It's not starting.

27:11.440 --> 27:13.080
- You filled it up?
- Mmm, yeah, I did.

27:13.680 --> 27:16.320
- Let's go.
- Come on, come on, come on, come on.

27:16.400 --> 27:19.960
I could have got a car,
but a man should never forget his status.

30:00.000 --> 30:10.000
ভুয়া লিংক এড়িয়ে চলুন — অফিসিয়াল: -=[ MyFlixBD.com ]=-
